---
/**
 * Players Guide - Worlds & Travel
 */
import GuideLayout from '../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
---

<GuideLayout title="Worlds & Travel" currentPage="worlds" description="Learn about BlockHaven's different worlds and how to travel between them">
  <h1>Worlds & Travel</h1>
  <p class="text-xl !text-text-light mb-8">
    BlockHaven features multiple worlds to explore. Learn how to navigate between them and what each offers.
  </p>

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>World Overview</h2>
    <p>
      BlockHaven uses the Multiverse plugin to offer multiple unique worlds. Each world has its own
      purpose, difficulty, and features.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-gold/10 border border-primary-gold/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 !text-primary-gold">Important: Separate Inventories</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        <strong>Inventories and experience are NOT shared between worlds.</strong> When you travel to a
        different world, you'll have a separate inventory, health, hunger, and XP. This means there's
        no gameplay advantage to teleporting - it's simply there to keep your experience fresh as you
        explore our various worlds!
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="spawn-hub">
    <h2>The Spawn Hub</h2>
    <p>
      The Spawn Hub is the central connection point for all worlds. When you first join BlockHaven,
      this is where you'll arrive. From here, you can access any world through physical portals.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Central location</strong> - All world portals are located here</li>
      <li><strong>Information center</strong> - Signs explain each world</li>
      <li><strong>Safe zone</strong> - No mobs or PvP in the hub</li>
      <li><strong>Community area</strong> - Meet other players and chat</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="survival-worlds">
    <h2>Survival Worlds</h2>
    <p>
      BlockHaven offers three Survival worlds with different difficulty levels.
      Choose the challenge that's right for you!
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/30 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Easy</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-2">Perfect for beginners or relaxed gameplay</p>
        <ul class="text-sm !mb-0 !ml-0">
          <li>Mobs deal less damage</li>
          <li>Hunger depletes slowly</li>
          <li>Health regenerates faster</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-400 mb-2">Normal</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-2">The standard Minecraft experience</p>
        <ul class="text-sm !mb-0 !ml-0">
          <li>Balanced difficulty</li>
          <li>Standard mob damage</li>
          <li>Regular hunger mechanics</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/30 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-400 mb-2">Hard</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-2">For experienced players seeking challenge</p>
        <ul class="text-sm !mb-0 !ml-0">
          <li>Mobs deal more damage</li>
          <li>Zombies can break doors</li>
          <li>Spiders can spawn with buffs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Survival World Features</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Safe zones</strong> - Each world has a protected spawn area where mobs can't hurt you</li>
      <li><strong>Nether access</strong> - Build a Nether portal to explore the Nether dimension</li>
      <li><strong>End access</strong> - Find the stronghold to access the End and fight the dragon</li>
      <li><strong>Land claims</strong> - Protect your builds in all survival worlds</li>
      <li><strong>Jobs & Economy</strong> - Earn money while you play</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="creative-worlds">
    <h2>Creative Worlds</h2>
    <p>
      Creative worlds are perfect for building and exploring without the survival mechanics.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-accent-diamond/10 border border-accent-diamond/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 text-accent-diamond">Peaceful Building</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        Creative worlds are set to <strong>Peaceful difficulty</strong>, meaning no hostile mobs will spawn.
        You're free to build and explore without worrying about monsters!
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Creative World Features</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Unlimited resources</strong> - Access to all blocks and items</li>
      <li><strong>Flight</strong> - Double-tap jump to fly</li>
      <li><strong>No hunger</strong> - Focus on building without survival needs</li>
      <li><strong>Instant breaking</strong> - Remove blocks instantly</li>
      <li><strong>Land claims</strong> - Yes, claims work in Creative too!</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="traveling">
    <h2>Traveling Between Worlds</h2>
    <p>
      There are two ways to travel between worlds on BlockHaven:
    </p>

    <h3>Method 1: Physical Portals</h3>
    <p>
      The Spawn Hub contains portals to every world. Simply walk through the portal for your destination.
      Each portal is labeled with the world name and difficulty.
    </p>

    <h3>Method 2: Teleport Commands</h3>
    <p>
      All players have permission to use the <code>/mvtp</code> command to teleport directly to any world.
      This is convenient when you want to quickly switch between worlds without returning to the hub.
    </p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/mvtp [world]</code></td>
          <td>Teleport directly to a world</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/mv list</code></td>
          <td>List all available worlds</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0">Example Usage</h4>
      <p>To teleport to the easy survival world:</p>
      <code>/mvtp survival_easy</code>
      <p class="!mb-0 mt-4 text-sm">
        Use <code>/mv list</code> to see the exact names of all worlds.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="inventory-info">
    <h2>Per-World Inventories</h2>
    <p>
      Each world maintains its own separate inventory. This means:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Items don't transfer</strong> - Your diamond pickaxe in one world won't be in another</li>
      <li><strong>Experience is separate</strong> - XP earned in one world stays in that world</li>
      <li><strong>Health and hunger reset</strong> - Each world has independent survival stats</li>
      <li><strong>Enderchests are shared</strong> - Within the same inventory group, enderchests may be linked</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-primary-gold/10 border border-primary-gold/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 !text-primary-gold">Why Separate Inventories?</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        Separate inventories ensure fair gameplay. You can't farm resources in Easy mode and use them
        in Hard mode, keeping each world's progression meaningful. It also prevents Creative mode items
        from entering Survival worlds.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="world-specific-homes">
    <h2>Homes and Teleportation</h2>
    <p>
      Your <code>/home</code> locations are world-specific. Setting a home in one world only works in that world.
    </p>

    <h3>Useful Commands</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/sethome [name]</code></td>
          <td>Set a home in current world</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/home [name]</code></td>
          <td>Teleport to your home in current world</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/spawn</code></td>
          <td>Return to current world's spawn</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/tpa [player]</code></td>
          <td>Request teleport to player (same world only)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="tips">
    <h2>World Travel Tips</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Store important items</strong> - Before switching worlds, make sure valuable items are safe</li>
      <li><strong>Use enderchests</strong> - Enderchests can help transfer some items within inventory groups</li>
      <li><strong>Set homes in each world</strong> - Have a home set in every world you play in regularly</li>
      <li><strong>Try different difficulties</strong> - Each survival world offers a unique experience</li>
      <li><strong>Explore Creative</strong> - Use Creative worlds to test build designs before building in Survival</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="next-steps">
    <h2>Explore More</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
      <a href="/worlds" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">World Details</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">See detailed information about each world including features and settings.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/guide" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Quick Start</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Go back to the basics and get started on your BlockHaven adventure.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</GuideLayout>
